-- Indiana Tops No. 1 Michigan, Oklahoma State Ends Kansas Streak
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2013-02-03T05:00:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-03/indiana-tops-no-1-michigan-oklahoma-state-ends-kansas-streak.html
Indiana  University knocked off top-
ranked University of  Michigan  81-73 while Oklahoma State
University stopped the No. 2 University of Kansas’ 18-game win
streak with an 85-80 victory in college basketball games.  In other games involving top-five teams last night, it was
No. 4 Florida 78, No. 16 Mississippi 64 and No. 5 Duke 79,
Florida State 60.  Cody Zeller scored 19 points and Victor Oladipo added 15 as
the third-ranked Hoosiers defeated Michigan in their Big Ten
Conference contest at Assembly Hall in Bloomington, Indiana.  Indiana improved to 8-1 in the Big Ten with Michigan at 7-2
in the conference, and both teams are now 20-2 overall.  Each Hoosiers starter scored at least 11 points, including
Christian Watford and Kevin Ferrell with 14 apiece and Jordan
Hulls scoring 11.  Trey Burke led the Wolverines with 25 points and Tim
Hardaway Jr. added 18.  In the other upset, Markel Brown scored 28 points and
Marcus Smart added 25 as Oklahoma State (15-5, 5-3 Big 12) ended
the Jayhawks’ 33-game home winning streak at Allen Fieldhouse in
Lawrence,  Kansas .  The Cowboys trailed 66-62 until they went on a run that
gave them a 73-68 lead with just over a minute left in the game.  Ben McLemore had 23 points and Kevin Young added 12 for
Kansas, which fell to 19-2 and 7-1 in the conference.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
